The paper presents a platform for interactive visualization of large graphs, which involves offline preprocessing, spatial data structures, and efficient spatial operations. This work is relevant to several subfields of computer science, including database systems (cs.DB) for the storage and retrieval of graph data, information retrieval (cs.IR) for the keyword search functionality, data structures (cs.DS) for the indexing of nodes and abstraction layers, human-computer interaction (cs.HCI) for the interactive navigation and exploration of the graph, and computational geometry (cs.CG) for the use of Euclidean plane and R-trees.
